## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Android Studio
- Java SDK
- Basic knowledge of Android development

### Installation

1. **Clone the Repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/shreyas6578/Calculator.git
   ```

2. **Open the Project in Android Studio:**

   - Open Android Studio.
   - Navigate to `File -> Open`, then find and select the cloned repository.

3. **Build the App:**

   - Ensure that your Android Studio is set up with the appropriate Android SDK.
   - Click on the Run button to build and deploy the app to your Android device or emulator.

